{
  "texts": [
    "Speech ExpressionSpeech delivers emotional information through linguistic and acoustic messages that reflect how the words are spoken [39].",
    "The linguistic content of speech carries emotional information.",
    "Some of the information can be inferred directly from the surface features of the words, which have been summarized in emotional words dictionaries [40].",
    "The rest of the information lies under the text surface and can only be understood when considering semantic contexts (e.g., discourse information).",
    "Although the association between linguistic content and emotion is language-dependent, multiple cross-lingual models have been developed for emotion detection [41,42]."
  ]
}